# Stack and UI conventions

## Core stack (use unless SPEC or user explicitly changes it)

| Layer | Choice |
|-------|--------|
| Framework | **Next.js** (App Router), deploy on **Vercel** |
| Data / auth / files | **Supabase** (Postgres, Auth, Storage, **RLS**) |
| Payments | **Stripe** (EUR); webhooks in Route Handlers |
| Email | **Resend** (transactional) |
| Drops / queues | **Upstash** (Redis / QStash) per **SPEC.md** §5–6 |

## UI

- **Tailwind CSS** for styling.
- **shadcn/ui** for accessible primitives (Button, Dialog, Form, etc.); extend patterns from existing components—avoid one-off raw HTML for complex controls when a shadcn pattern exists.
- **Responsive first:** SPEC targets strong mobile and desktop; test layouts at common breakpoints.
- **i18n:** Spanish and English on customer-facing surfaces per SPEC.

## Integration discipline

- **Stripe / Resend / Supabase service role** run **server-side only** (Route Handlers, Server Actions, server components that do not leak secrets). Follow the Cursor rule **secrets-environment**.
